                            <comment id="17428282" author="xmarker" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:04:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;May be&#160;KafkaRecordSerializationSchemaWrapper.serialize called a incorrect&#160;ProducerRecord construct method,I can help fix this issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17428283" author="fabian.paul" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2021 15:10:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=xmarker&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;xmarker&quot;&gt;xmarker&lt;/a&gt; yes you are right. We need to always use a constructor with a timestamp and set it. AFAIK the constructor fields of the ProducerRecord are all nullable. I assign you the ticket and I can help to review it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
